{"lemma":"ذِراعٌ","slug":"ذِراعٌ","root":"ذ.ر.ع","root_slug":"ذ-ر-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ذ-ر-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ذِراع","root":"ذرع","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13805","n13806","n13813"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B0%D9%90%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the limb of any animal, an arm or leg","tags":["countable"],"examples":[{"text":"لِلْأُخْطُبُوطِ ثَمَانِي أَذْرُعٍ.","english":"Octopuses have eight arms."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the limb of any animal, an arm or leg; the portion of the upper appendage from the shoulder to wrist, the arm","tags":["countable"],"examples":[{"text":"فِي ذِرَاعِ ٱلْإِنْسَانِ ثَلَاثَةُ عِظَامٍ: اِثْنَتَانِ فِي ٱلسَّاعِدِ ٱسْمَاهُمَا ٱلزَّنْدُ وَٱلْكُعْبُرَةُ وَوَاحِدَةٌ فِي ٱلْعَضُدِ.","english":"There are three bones in the human arm: two in the lower arm (called the ulna and the radius) and one in the upper arm."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the limb of any animal, an arm or leg; something resembling, likened to, or related to an arm or arms (such as a lever, a shift lever, a lever arm, a crank arm, a jib, a boom, a branch or division, power, might, influence, and so on)","tags":["broadly","countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the portion of the upper appendage from the elbow to the wrist, the lower arm, the forearm","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a cubit, especially the Arabian cubit variously standardized by place, time, and item from 25–75 cm (10 in–2 ft 6 in).","tags":["countable"],"examples":[{"text":"ثُمَّ فِي سِلْسِلَةٍ ذَرْعُهَا سَبْعُونَ ذِرَاعًا فَٱسْلُكُوهُ"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate to Aramaic דְּרָעָא / ܕܪܥܐ (dərāʿā), Hebrew זְרוֹעַ (zərṓaʿ), Ugaritic 𐎏𐎗𐎓 (ḏrʿ), Ge'ez መዝራዕት (mäzraʿt), Tigre ዘራዕ (zäraʿ), መዛርዕት (mäzarəʿt), Tigrinya መዝራዕት (mäzraʿt), Soqotri direʿ, Shehri diráʿ."},"ipa":["/ði.raːʕ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13805","headword_ar":"ذَرَاعٌ","root":"*rE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAEN","text_ar":"ذِرَاعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, K) (assumed tropical:)  A woman (S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active, with the hands in spinning:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who spins much; who has ability to do so."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","ISd"]},{"entry_id":"n13806","headword_ar":"ذِرَاعٌ","root":"*rE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", of a man, (Msb,) [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the elbow to the extremities of the fingers;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fore arm;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAEidN","text_ar":"سَاعِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.; thus corresponding to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAq","text_ar":"سَاق"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the leg]: (Lth, K:) and (tropical:)  [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"space"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the extremity of the elbow to the extremity of the middle finger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, * K: [in the last of which, the space is plainly shown to be meant, like as the part is shown in the Msb to be meant in the explanation cited above from that work and the Mgh: see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jariybN","text_ar":"جَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) in both these senses, sometimes masc., (K,) accord. to Kh: (TA:) J says, (TA,) as relating to the arm, it is masc. and fem.; but Sb says that it is fem.: (S, TA:) [Mtr says,] it is fem.: (Mgh:) [Fei says,] the measure so called is in most instances fem.: accord. to ISk, it is fem.; but some of the Arabs make it masc.: Fr says that it is fem.; but that some of [the tribe named] 'Okl make it masc.: As did not know an instance of its being masc.: and Zj says that such an instance is extr.; not choice: (Msb:) the measure thus called, [i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cubit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Msb,) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAEN mukas~arap","text_ar":"ذِرَاعٌ مُكَسَّرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cubit which is divided into fractions"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Mgh,) is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"six"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDaAt","text_ar":"قَبَضَات"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fists"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Mgh, Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of middling measure;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and this is"},{"kind":"page_break","n":962},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAEu AlEamaAm~api","text_ar":"ذِرَاعُ العَمَامَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the cubit of the common people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the common cubit"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"because it wants one"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDap","text_ar":"قَبْضَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fist"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of what is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAEu Almaliki","text_ar":"ذِرَاعُ المَلِكِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the cubit of the king"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"namely one of the Kisràs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not the last of them, whose"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*rAE","text_ar":"ذراع"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was seven"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDaAt","text_ar":"قَبَضَات"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miylN","text_ar":"مِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": it is also an astronomical measure; and as such, it seems, from several instances in which it is mentioned by Kzw and other writers, to be, probably, by rule,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two degrees;"},{"kind":"text","text":"nearly the half, or quarter, of the length assigned in different instances to the measure termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rumoHN","text_ar":"رُمْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but, like the latter, not precise nor uniform in every instance:] the dim. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uriy~aEapN","text_ar":"ذُرِيَّعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it is fem.; (TA;) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*urayoEN","text_ar":"ذُرَيْعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uray~iEN","text_ar":"ذُرَيِّعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to those who make it masc.]: (L voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarobN","text_ar":"حَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*oruEN","text_ar":"اَذْرُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uroEaAnN","text_ar":"ذُرْعَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, Msb, K;) or, accord. to Sb, the former only; (S, Msb;) and Sb adds, they have given it this form of pl. because it is fem.; meaning, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEaAlN","text_ar":"فِعَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEaAlN","text_ar":"فُعَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", when fem., have the pl. of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEulN","text_ar":"اَفْعُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) In the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~awobu saboEN fiY vamaAniyapK","text_ar":"الثَّوْبُ سَبْعٌ فِى ثَمَانِيَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth, is seven"},{"kind":"text","text":"cubits"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by eight"},{"kind":"text","text":"spans], they say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sbE","text_ar":"سبع"},{"kind":"text","text":"because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*oruE","text_ar":"اَذْرُع"},{"kind":"text","text":"is fem., and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vmAnyp","text_ar":"ثمانية"},{"kind":"text","text":"because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$obaAr","text_ar":"اَشْبَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"is masc.; (S; [and the like is said in the Mgh;]) and because the length is measured by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*rAE","text_ar":"ذراع"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the breadth by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ibor","text_ar":"شِبْر"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vmn","text_ar":"ثمن"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAEN","text_ar":"ذِرَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used as an epithet, applied to a masc. n.: thus they say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA vawobN *iraAEN","text_ar":"هٰذَا ثَوْبٌ ذِرَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth, a cubit in length"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Kh.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa min~iY EalaY Haboli Al*~iraAEi","text_ar":"هُوَ مِنِّى عَلَى حَبْلِ الذِّرَاعِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is prepared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made ready, on my part:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa laka EalaY Haboli Al*~iraAEi","text_ar":"هُوَ لَكَ عَلَى حَبْلِ الذِّرَاعِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will pay it to thee in ready money:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is prepared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made ready, for thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hbl","text_ar":"حبل"},{"kind":"text","text":"being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain vein in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*rAE","text_ar":"ذراع"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence several tropical significations:] see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aroEN","text_ar":"ذَرْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in six places: and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*araAEN","text_ar":"ذَرَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  Hence also, (Z, TA,) (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"instrument with which one measures the length of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*rAE","text_ar":"ذراع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cubit"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, Z, O, Mgh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made of a piece of wood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether it be iron or a rod of wood."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) ―         -b4-  [Hence also,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sleeve:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN muwa$~aY Al*~iraAEi","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ مُوَشَّى الذِّرَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth, variegated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"figured, in the sleeve"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: pl. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*aAriEu","text_ar":"مَذَارِعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", a pl. not agreeing with its sing., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malaAmiHu","text_ar":"مَلَامِحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maHaAsinu","text_ar":"مَحَاسِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b5-  Of the fore legs of bulls or cows, and of sheep or goats, [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arm;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part above the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuraAE","text_ar":"كُرَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":": and of the fore legs of camels and horses and mules and asses, [likewise the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arm;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part above the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waZiyf","text_ar":"وَظِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) [also the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arm-bone"},{"kind":"text","text":"of any of the animals here mentioned:] accord. to Lth, (TA,) of any animal, [but this is by synecdoche, (assumed tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fore leg;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadN","text_ar":"يَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, TA;) applying to the whole of whatever is called thus: (TA:) [thus, again, corresponding to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAqN","text_ar":"سَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; this latter term, in like manner, having a proper and a synecdochical acceptation. Hence the prov.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tuToEimi AlEaboda","text_ar":"لَا تُطْعِمِ العَبْدَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkuraAEa fayaTomaEa fiY Al*~iraAEi","text_ar":"الكُرَاعَ فَيَطْمَعَ فِى الذِّرَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Feed not thou the slave with the shank, lest he covet the arm"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b6-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~iraAEu","text_ar":"الذِّرَاعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAEu AlA^asad","text_ar":"ذِرَاعُ الاَسَد"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two bright stars, which are one of the Mansions of the Moon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) [there are two asterisms thus called; together,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~iraEaAni","text_ar":"الذِّرَعَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": one of them is]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~iraAEu AlmabosuwTapu","text_ar":"الذِّرَاعُ المَبْسُوطَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAEu AlA^asadi AlmabosuwTapu","text_ar":"ذِرَاعُ الاَسَدِ المَبْسُوطَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two bright stars"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"α and        \n      β"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the heads of Gemini:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kzw in his description of Gemini:) [the other is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~iraAEu AlmaqobuwDapu","text_ar":"الذِّرَاعُ المَقْبُوضَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAEu AlA^asadi AlmaqobuwDapu","text_ar":"ذِرَاعُ الاَسَدِ المَقْبُوضَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two bright stars"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"α and        \n      β"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Canis Minor:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kzw in his description of Canis Minor:) [hence it appears that the ancient Arabs, or many of them, extended the figure of Leo (as they did also that of Scorpio) far beyond the limits which we assign to it: the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*rAE","text_ar":"ذراع"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to those who make"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~awo'u","text_ar":"النَّوْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to signify “ the auroral rising, ” but the latter accord. to those who make it to signify “ the auroral setting, ” is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Seventh Mansion of the Moon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the following descriptions in Kzw's account of the Mansions of the Moon, and in the O and K and TA, are obscure and inaccurate:]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~iraAEu","text_ar":"الذِّرَاعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the Mansions of the Moon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, Kzw, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*rAE AlAsd","text_ar":"ذراع الاسد"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmqbwDp","text_ar":"المقبوضة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, Kzw,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*rAE AlAsd AlmbswTp","text_ar":"ذراع الاسد المبسوطة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the lion has a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*rAE","text_ar":"ذراع"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mbswTp","text_ar":"مبسوطة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*rAE","text_ar":"ذراع"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mqbwDp","text_ar":"مقبوضة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, Kzw, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and this is the one next to Syria,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the left,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kzw,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in it the moon has a mansion; the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mbswTp","text_ar":"مبسوطة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being next to El-Yemen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the right;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kzw;) [but this description of their relative positions should be reversed, as is shown by what precedes and by what follows;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"each being two stars, between which is the measure of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawoT","text_ar":"سَوْط"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whip"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (O;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the latter is higher in the sky, and more extended, than the other,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wherefore it is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mbswTp","text_ar":"مبسوطة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and sometimes the moon deviates, and so has a mansion in it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) [it is said in the TA that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*rAE","text_ar":"الذراع"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also a name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the asterisms"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nujuwm","text_ar":"نُجُوم"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljawozaA='","text_ar":"الجَوْزَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this is the same that is called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mbswTp","text_ar":"مبسوطة"},{"kind":"text","text":":]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it rises"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at dawn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the fourth of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tam~uwz","text_ar":"تَمُّوز"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"July O. S."},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and sets"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at dawn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the fourth of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAnuwn AlA=xir","text_ar":"كَانُون الا=خِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"January, O. S."},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (O, Kzw: [and so in the K, except that in this last, it is erroneously said to set in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAnuwn AlA^aw~al","text_ar":"كَانُون الاَوَّل"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) so says IKt: but Ibráheem El-Harbee says that it rises on the seventh of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tm~wz","text_ar":"تمّوز"},{"kind":"text","text":", and sets on the sixth of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kAnwn","text_ar":"كانون"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA=xr","text_ar":"الا=خر"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, TA.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaAzilu Alqamari","text_ar":"مَنَازِلُ القَمَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nzl","text_ar":"نزل"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawo'N","text_ar":"نَوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nakobaA='u","text_ar":"نَكْبَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] The rhyming prosaist of the Arabs says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA TalaEati Al*~iraAEo Hasarati Al$~amosu","text_ar":"اـِذَا طَلَعَتِ الذِّرَاعْ حَسَرَتِ الشَّمْسُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqinaAEo waA@sotaEolato fiY AlA^ufuqi Al$~uEaAEo wa taraqoraqa Als~araAbu fiY","text_ar":"القِنَاعْ وَا@سْتَعْلَتْ فِى الاُفُقِ الشُّعَاعْ وَ تَرَقْرَقَ السَّرَابُ فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~i qaAEo","text_ar":"كُلِّ قَاعْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When the Dhiráa rises"},{"kind":"text","text":"at dawn,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the sun puts off the veil, and the rays ascend in the horizon, and the mirage flickers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"glistens, in every plain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And the Arabs assert that when there is no rain [at any other season] in the year, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*rAE","text_ar":"ذراع"},{"kind":"text","text":"does not break its promise, though it be but a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bago$ap","text_ar":"بَغْشَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or weak shower of rain]: (Kzw, TA:) [or] its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawo'","text_ar":"نَوْء"},{"kind":"text","text":"is approved, and seldom does it break its promise. (Kzw.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAEN","text_ar":"ذِرَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain mark made with a hot iron upon the arm"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*rAE","text_ar":"ذراع"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a camel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) and is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mark of the Benoo-Thaalebeh in El-Yemen, and of some persons of the Benoo-Málik-Ibn-Saad."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b8-  Also (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fore part of a spear"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spear-shaft:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) this is called (S, TA) also (TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAEu AlaEaAmili","text_ar":"ذِرَاعُ الَعَامِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","Lth","K","TA","S","Mgh","Z","O","Kzw"]},{"entry_id":"n13813","headword_ar":"ذَرَّاعٌ","root":"*rE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A measurer with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAE","text_ar":"ذِرَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cubit"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^br","text_ar":"ابر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  A he-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that drives the she-camel with his arm and so makes her lie down that he may cover her."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}